displaytitle: Black Hero: Brooklyn's Congresswoman-elect Mrs. Shirley Chisholm unveils a plaque for an "Unknown Hero" at the U.S. Customs House in New York City, December 19, 1968. The ceremony was organized by Negro History Associated, Inc., to commemorate a moment in the history of early New York when an unidentified Negro uncovered a plot to destroy Fort New Amsterdam in 1689
creditline: Gift of M. Robin Krasny, Class of 1973
inscribed: With typewritten title and typewritten label with title and date affixed to verso
